#X text 1364 434 LINEAR FREQEUNCY RANGE -> TOO HARD TO MAKE IT LOGARITHMIC \, MEANING TO HAVE AS AN EXAMPLE SAME DISTANCE BETWEEN 200 TO 400 AND 400 TO 800 (SPACING BASED ON OCTAVE) \; BASICALLY TO DO THIS \, THE 4096 ARRAY GOT FROM THE FFT~ OBJECT \, SHOULD BE PLACED ON AN X AXIS THAT K=10 AND K=20 HAVE SAME DISTANCING AS K=20 AND K=40. NOT POSSIBLE IN PD! \; WHY WE MIGHT WANT TO DO LOGARITHMIC FREQUENCY RANGE? -> DUE TO LIMITED SCREEN SIZE \, IF I WANT TO SHOW WHOLE 20kHz HUMAN RANGE EVERYTHING WILL BE REALLY SQUISHED! -> LOGARIGTHMI SCALE OF X AXIS GIVES MORE SPACING TO LOW FREQUENCIES AND LESS TO HIGH (1000 - 2000Hz (1000Hz) WILL HAVE SAME SPACING AS 10000 - 20000Hz (10000Hz))!;
